----- Original Message -----
> From: "Setia Pramana" <setia.pramana at ki.se>
> To: bioc-devel at r-project.org
> Sent: Wednesday, December 4, 2013 8:40:51 AM
> Subject: [Bioc-devel] How to update a release package?
> 
> Dear All,
> I made a modification of the development page (neaGUI). But It seems
> the release version is not updated. Please let me know how can I
> update or modify the release version?
> Thank you in advanced for your help!


I don't see any commits to either release or devel. 
Note that if you make a commit to devel, nothing changes in release. This is by design.

Only bug fixes and documentation enhancements should be committed to release; all other changes should go in devel. 

That said, if you really want to commit a change to both release and devel, see
http://www.bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/source-control/

